<div id="v10.1.11"><span class="H430 s">And </span><span class="TheLordTitles"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H559 s"> </span></span><span class="H559 s">said</span><span class="H776 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> </span><span class="TheLordWords"><span class="H776 s">Let the earth</span><span class="H1876 s"> bring forth</span><span class="H1877 s"> grass</span><span class="H6212 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> the herb</span><span class="H2232 s"> yielding</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H6529 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> <i>and</i> the fruit</span><span class="H6086 s"> tree</span><span class="H6213 s"> yielding</span><span class="H6529 s"> fruit</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H834 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> whose</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H776 s"> <i>is</i> in itself<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> upon the earth</span><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span> </span>and it was so. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> <span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">(</span></span></span>grass<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> Heb<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span> tender grass<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">)</span></span></span></span></div> 
<div id="v10.1.12"><span class="H776 s">And the earth</span><span class="H3318 s"> brought forth</span><span class="H1877 s"> grass</span><span class="H6212 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> <i>and</i> herb</span><span class="H2232 s"> yielding</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H4327 s"> after his kind</span><span class="H6086 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and the tree</span><span class="H6213 s"> yielding</span><span class="H6529 s"> fruit</span><span class="H2233 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> whose seed</span><span class="H4327 s"> <i>was</i> in itself<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> after his kind</span><span class="H430 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> and </span><span class="TheLordTitles"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H7200 s"> </span></span><span class="H7200 s">saw</span><span class="H2896 s"> that <i>it was</i> good</span>.</div> 
