<div id="v10.1.16"><span class="H430 s">And </span><span class="TheLordTitles"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H6213 s"> </span></span><span class="H6213 s">made</span><span class="H8147 s"> two</span><span class="H1419 s"> great</span><span class="H3974 s"> lights</span><span class="H1419 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">;</span></span></span> the greater</span><span class="H3974 s"> light</span><span class="H4475 s"> to rule</span><span class="H3117 s"> the day</span><span class="H6996 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and the lesser</span><span class="H3974 s"> light</span><span class="H4475 s"> to rule</span><span class="H3915 s"> the night</span><span class="H3556 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> <span class="TheLordTitles"><i>he </i></span><i>made</i> the stars</span> also. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> <span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">(</span></span></span>to rule the day…<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> Heb<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span> for the rule of the day<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> etc<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">)</span></span></span></span></div> 
