<div id="v10.1.28"><span class="H430 s">And </span><span class="TheLordTitles"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H1288 s"> </span></span><span class="H1288 s">blessed</span><span class="H430 s"> them<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and </span><span class="TheLordTitles"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H559 s"> </span></span><span class="H559 s">said</span><span class="H6509 s"> unto them<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> </span><span class="TheLordWords"><span class="H6509 s">Be fruitful</span><span class="H7235 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and multiply</span><span class="H4390 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and replenish</span><span class="H776 s"> the earth</span><span class="H3533 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and subdue it</span><span class="H7287 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> and have dominion</span><span class="H1710 s"> over the fish</span><span class="H3220 s"> of the sea</span><span class="H5775 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and over the fowl</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the air</span><span class="H2416 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and over every living thing</span><span class="H7430 s"> that moveth</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span>. </span><span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> <span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">(</span></span></span>moveth<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> Heb<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span> creepeth<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">)</span></span></span></span></div> 
<div id="v10.1.29"><span class="H430 s">And </span><span class="TheLordTitles"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H559 s"> </span></span><span class="H559 s">said</span><span class="H2009 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> </span><span class="TheLordWords"><span class="H2009 s">Behold</span><span class="H5414 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> I have given</span><span class="H6212 s"> you every herb</span><span class="H2232 s"> bearing</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H6440 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> which <i>is</i> upon the face</span><span class="H776 s"> of all the earth</span><span class="H6086 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and every tree</span><span class="H6529 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> in the which <i>is</i> the fruit</span><span class="H6086 s"> of a tree</span><span class="H2232 s"> yielding</span><span class="H2233 s"> seed</span><span class="H1961 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">;</span></span></span> to you it shall be</span><span class="H402 s"> for meat</span>. </span><span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> <span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">(</span></span></span>bearing…<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> Heb<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span> seeding seed<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">)</span></span></span> <span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">(</span></span></span>yielding…<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> Heb<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span> seeding seed<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">)</span></span></span></span></div> 
<div id="v10.1.30"><span class="H2416 s"></span><span class="TheLordWords"><span class="H2416 s">And to every beast</span><span class="H776 s"> of the earth</span><span class="H5775 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and to every fowl</span><span class="H8064 s"> of the air</span><span class="H7430 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and to every thing that creepeth</span><span class="H776 s"> upon the earth</span><span class="H2416 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> wherein <i>there is</i> life</span><span class="H5315 s"> †</span><span class="H3418 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> <i>I have given</i> every green</span><span class="H6212 s"> herb</span><span class="H402 s"> for meat</span></span>: and it was so. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> <span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">(</span></span></span>life<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">:</span></span></span> Heb<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span> a living soul<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">)</span></span></span></span></div> 
<div id="v10.1.31"><span class="H430 s">And </span><span class="TheLordTitles"><span class="H430 s">God</span><span class="H7200 s"> </span></span><span class="H7200 s">saw</span><span class="H834 s"> every thing that</span><span class="H6213 s"> <span class="TheLordTitles">he </span>had made</span><span class="H3966 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> and<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> behold<span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">,</span></span></span> <i>it was</i> very</span><span class="H2896 s"> good</span><span class="H6153 s"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation"><span class="punctuation">.</span></span></span> And the evening</span><span class="H1242 s"> and the morning</span><span class="H8345 s"> were the sixth</span><span class="H3117 s"> day</span>.</div></div>
